I noticed Voidtrain quite a long time ago on YouTube. If my memory serves me correctly, the game was not yet on Steam.

From what I liked I can note the following:
- atmospheric. Yes, the game is definitely atmospheric;
- great visual style. Reminds me of Steampunk;
- the slow movement of the train and the quaint world around leave a pleasant impression. You can meditate) ;
- music. She is good;
- crafting weapons;
- the main concept of the game is cool, but there are some things that need to be worked on. More on this further:

What I didn't like:
- grind. I don't like grind, especially when there is a lot of it
- the point of improving the train is not entirely clear. You still have to drive slowly to collect resources
- same enemies and repeating events. It's like they just copied the same thing

The developers definitely need to add more variety of events to the game.
The game lacks variety in many aspects.
However, the first 10-15 hours of the game will be quite exciting
